Got it — much cleaner. Customer master as the spine (for holdout), left join the two txn tables, flags derived directly, simple CASE for segment.

```sql
-- ================================================================
-- CAR_960 | Spain Owned Stores | Target Audience Build
-- ================================================================


-- Table 1: Digital transactions — one row per customer, most recent txn date
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE CAR_960_DIGITAL_TXN AS
SELECT
    opacket_sc_galacticid               AS customer_key,
    MAX(DATE(opacket_transactiontime))  AS last_digital_txn_date
FROM WUDNA.SUMMARY_GEN.MATCHEDTRANSACTION_OPACKET_VW
WHERE opacket_sender_country = 'ES'
  AND opacket_sender_city IN (
        'MADRID CAPITAL','LA CORUÑA','MOLLABAO PONTEVEDRA','SAN PEDRO MARBELLA',
        'LLUTXENT- VALENCIA','PROVINCIA DE MADRID','MUNICIPIO DE MADRID','ALDAIA VALENCIA',
        'ALBAL VALENCIA','VALENCIA CAPITAL','OPORTO MADRID','EL PERELLONET-VALENCIA',
        'LA ELIANA VALENCIA','LAS ROZAS  DE MADRID','LEGANÉS MADRID','MADRID, ALCOBENDAS',
        'MARBELLA NUEVA ANDALUCIA','PUZOL VALENCIA','BUNOL VALENCIA','VALENCIA CENTRO',
        'BENIMACLET - VALENCIA','ALCOBENDAS MADRID','ROCAFORT, VALENCIA','TORRENT VALENCIA',
        'VALENCIA CATARROJA','VITORIA- GASTEIZ','GANDIA , VALENCIA','BUNOL-VALENCIA',
        'MADRID MOSTOLES','MADRID GETAFE','VALENCIA ESPAÑA','BENIMAMET-VALENCIA',
        'NAQUERA VALENCIA','MARBELLA','BARRO PONTEVEDRA','TRES CANTOS- MADRID',
        'MADRID','MAJADAHONDA MADRID','VIGO PONTEVEDRA','MADRID MADRID','CHESTE VALENCIA',
        'PONTEVEDRA CAPITAL','ENGUERA VALENCIA','VITORIA-GASTEIZ','VALENCIA ALCASSER',
        'ALGINET VALENCIA','VITORIA','COMUNIDAD DE MADRID','VALDEMORO, MADRID','PONTEVEDRA',
        'A CORUÑA','CORUÑA','LAS ROZAS DE MADRID','MISLATA VALENCIA',
        'NUEVA ANDALUCIA, MARBELLA','MADRID CITY','HUMANES DE MADRID','LALIN PONTEVEDRA',
        'RIO REAL MARBELLA','MADRID CENTRO','MARIN PONTEVEDRA','Madrid','PARLA MADRID',
        'MISLATA, VALENCIA','VALENCIA, BENIMACLET','CIUDAD DE VALENCIA','VALENCIA',
        'VALENCIA ALFAFAR','MADRID, MADRID, ESPANA'
  )
  AND DATE(opacket_transactiontime) >= '2024-03-25'
  AND DATE(opacket_transactiontime) <  '2026-03-25'
GROUP BY 1;


-- Table 2: Retail transactions — one row per customer, most recent txn date
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE CAR_960_RETAIL_TXN AS
SELECT
    tx.sndcustomer_key                  AS customer_key,
    MAX(DATE(tx.RCVPAYING_DATETIME))    AS last_retail_txn_date
FROM WUDNA.SUMMARY_GEN.AGENT_SUMMARY_VW ag
JOIN WUDNA.SUMMARY_GEN.WUDNA_TXN_MASTER_ANALYTICS_VW tx
  ON ag.agent_number = tx.sndagent_number
WHERE UPPER(TRIM(ag.city)) IN ('MADRID','VITORIA','VALENCIA','MARBELLA','CORUNA','PONTEVEDRA')
  AND DATE(tx.RCVPAYING_DATETIME) >= '2024-03-25'
  AND DATE(tx.RCVPAYING_DATETIME) <  '2026-03-25'
GROUP BY 1;


-- Table 3: Final output
-- Base: all customers registered in target cities (drives RNT + pulls holdout)
-- Left join both txn tables → flags + segment assignment
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE CAR_960_FINAL AS
SELECT
    cm.customer_key,
    cm.global_holdout_flag,
    DATE(cm.first_registration_date)    AS first_registration_date,
    d.last_digital_txn_date,
    rt.last_retail_txn_date,
    CASE WHEN d.customer_key  IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_digital_txn,
    CASE WHEN rt.customer_key IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_retail_txn,
    CASE
        WHEN d.customer_key IS NULL
         AND rt.customer_key IS NULL
         AND DATE(cm.first_registration_date) >= '2024-03-25'  THEN 'RNT'
        WHEN d.last_digital_txn_date  >= '2025-03-25'
          OR rt.last_retail_txn_date  >= '2025-03-25'          THEN 'R12 Active'
        ELSE 'R13-R24 Lapsed'
    END AS segment
FROM WUDNA.SUMMARY_GEN.WUDNA_CUSTOMER_MASTER_VW cm
LEFT JOIN CAR_960_DIGITAL_TXN  d  ON d.customer_key  = cm.customer_key
LEFT JOIN CAR_960_RETAIL_TXN   rt ON rt.customer_key = cm.customer_key
WHERE UPPER(TRIM(cm.city)) IN ('MADRID','VITORIA','VALENCIA','MARBELLA','CORUNA','PONTEVEDRA');
```

---

Two things to note:

**RNT scope** — RNT only fires for customers registered within the last 2 years (`>= '2024-03-25'`). Customers registered earlier with no transactions fall into `'R13-R24 Lapsed'` by the ELSE. If you want to exclude those entirely, add `WHERE segment != 'R13-R24 Lapsed' OR last_digital_txn_date IS NOT NULL OR last_retail_txn_date IS NOT NULL` — but flag it with Camilla first.

**Transacted-not-registered** — since customer master is the LEFT spine, customers who transacted in these cities but registered with a different city won't appear. If Camilla confirms those should be included, we'd need a small UNION on the spine before the final join.
